Definition: a chemical reaction in which an acid and a base interact with the formation of a salt
Example: with strong acids and bases the essential reaction is the combination of hydrogen ions with hydroxyl ions to form water
Synonyms: verb, change, neutralize, neutralisation, neutralise, neutralization_reaction, neutralisation_reaction, chemical_reaction, a, chemical, reaction, in, which, an, acid, and, base, interact, with, the, formation, of, salt, strong, acids, bases, essential, is, combination, hydrogen, ions, hydroxyl, to, form, water
Category: noun.process
